	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Necro bump <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" /> 
<br />
<br />I am performing a RGB mod on a PAL french NES. Actualy it's done. But I have several issues and not tested yet others ways to obtain a RGB image.
<br />
<br />That I did :
<br />
<br />- swap cpu, ppu (rgb) and crystal from an US NES
<br />- cutting RGB pins on sony's chip
<br />- trace RGB line from 2c03 to RGB out of sony's chip
<br />- I use the sync directly on sony's chip
<br />
<br />I notice there allready have an RGB amp on power/vidéo box and I reused it... but no luck.
<br />
<br />TV switch to RGB mode but I have a black screen with sync but no image and no sound. Game boot fine, because I can hear sound when I take the signal directly from CPU.
<br />
<br />futher tests :
<br />
<br />- Place RGB lines from 2c03 directly on RGB pins of the AV connector and use an external amp
<br />- take sync signal directly from 2c03
<br />- test swapped cpu/ppu on PAL mobo with US AV box. (with origianl PPU)
<br />
<br />I notice there is a crystal in french NES AV box, can be use for vidéo sync purpose ?
<br />
<br />Photos on demand <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" />

		

